Ghana Builds Pipeline for Gas Processing Plant: Daily Graphic

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-04-29T11:42:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/ghana-builds-pipeline-for-gas-processing-plant-daily-graphic.html
Ghana completed construction of a
 gas pipeline  from the Jubilee oil field to a gas processing site
in the western town of Bonyere, Daily Graphic reported.  The 60-kilometer (37-mile) pipeline marks the first phase
of construction of a plant to process gas from the Jubilee
field, the Accra-based newspaper said, citing Nana Boakye Asafu- Adjaye, chief executive officer of the Ghana National Petroleum
Corp.  Oil production at the Jubilee field began on Dec. 15.
Output is expected to increase to 120,000 barrels per day by
July from 70,000 barrels currently, Stuart Wheaton, development
manager at Tullow Oil Ghana Ltd., said on April 12.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 